Feature: Canonical BC ".claude/settings.json" ships with "bd prime" as the sole "PreCompact" hook content

  Adds a new pin parallel to scenario 96 (canonical bc.json SessionStart = "bd prime") on the PreCompact key. No existing scenario currently pins anything under PreCompact for shop type "bc", so this scenario is additive. Mirrors scenario 97 (canonical lead.json PreCompact = "bd prime") for shop type "bc".

  The justification matches scenario 97: the PreCompact hook fires when Claude Code is about to compact conversation history; running "bd prime" at that moment refreshes the beads registry summary that the next post-compaction context will be primed against. The BC shop carries a beads registry on the same footing as the lead shop (scenario 50 pins "bd init --skip-agents" for every shop type at bootstrap), so the rationale applies symmetrically across shop types.

  Scenario: the canonical ".claude/settings.json" template for shop type "bc" declares "bd prime" as the sole inner-hook command under "PreCompact" and conforms to the Claude Code matcher+hooks wrapper schema
    When I ask the "shop-templates" package for the canonical ".claude/settings.json" template for shop type "bc" through its public template-access surface
    And the returned body is parsed as JSON
    Then the parsed value at top-level key "hooks" is a JSON object
    And the parsed value at "hooks.PreCompact" is a JSON array of length at least 1
    And exactly one JSON-object element of "hooks.PreCompact" has an inner "hooks" array containing an entry whose "command" string equals "bd prime"
    And every element of "hooks.PreCompact" is a JSON object with a "matcher" key whose value is a string and a "hooks" key whose value is a JSON array of length at least 1
